headlines.description: — Chelsea eased the pressure on manager Graham Potter by securing just a second Premier League victory since October with a 1-0 win over Crystal Palace at Stamford Bridge on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Chelsea beats Crystal Palace 1-0 to ease pressure on Potter

headlines.description: Club-record signing Alexander Isak came off the bench to earn Newcastle United a last-gasp 1-0 win over Fulham in the Premier League on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Isak earns Newcastle late win after Mitrovic error

headlines.description: — Arsenal extended its Premier League lead to eight points with a 2-0 win at Tottenham in the north London derby on Sunday that was helped by an own-goal by goalkeeper Hugo Lloris.
headlines.shortLinkText: Arsenal beats Tottenham 2-0 to stretch EPL lead to 8 points
